FBIS3-28526 "dreas026_n_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 Vietnam Radio Reports Returned Remains BK0802112694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 8 Feb 94 BK0802112694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Vietnam has handed over to the U.S. the remains of 12 U.S. servicemen reported missing in the Indochina war. Head of the Hanoi Task Force for MIA Colonel John Cray said the lifting of the embargo created more favorable conditions for his job in Vietnam. He also believed that Vietnam would now more actively cooperate with the U.S. to solve the MIA issue.
